### CRM Backend API Tests
### Requires VS Code "REST Client" extension or similar

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@adminToken = replace-with-admin-realm-token
@tenantId = replace-with-tenant-id

### --------------------------------------------------------
### Tenant Management (admin realm + CRM role required)
### --------------------------------------------------------

### Create Tenant
# @name createTenant
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Acme Corp",
    "slug": "acme",
    "description": "Pilot customer"
}

### Store Tenant ID
@createdTenantId = {{createTenant.response.body.id}}

### List Tenants
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/tenants?page=1&pageSize=20&status=active&q=acme
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get Tenant
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{createdTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Update Tenant
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{createdTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Acme Corporation",
    "description": "Upgraded account",
    "status": "active"
}

### Soft Delete Tenant
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### --------------------------------------------------------
### 1. Create a Lead Template
### --------------------------------------------------------
# @name createTemplate
POST {{baseUrl}}/templates
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "B2B Sales Lead"
}

### Store Template ID
@templateId = {{createTemplate.response.body.id}}

### --------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Add Dynamic Fields to the Template
### --------------------------------------------------------

### Field 1: Company Name (Required String)
POST {{baseUrl}}/templates/{{templateId}}/fields
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "companyName",
    "type": "string",
    "required": true
}

### Field 2: Contact Email (Email format)
POST {{baseUrl}}/templates/{{templateId}}/fields
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "contactEmail",
    "type": "string",
    "format": "email",
    "required": true
}

### Field 3: Expected Revenue (Currency format)
POST {{baseUrl}}/templates/{{templateId}}/fields
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "expectedRevenue",
    "type": "number",
    "format": "currency",
    "required": false
}

### --------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Get the Template Schema (For Frontend Dynamic Form)
### --------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/templates/{{templateId}}/schema

### --------------------------------------------------------
### 4. Create a Lead (Testing Dynamic Validation)
### --------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/leads
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "templateId": {{templateId}},
    "data": {
        "companyName": "Acme Corp",
        "contactEmail": "contact@acmecorp.com",
        "expectedRevenue": "50000.00"
    }
}

### --------------------------------------------------------
### 5. Create a Lead (Intentionally Fail Validation)
### --------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/leads
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "templateId": {{templateId}},
    "data": {
        "companyName": "Globex",
        "contactEmail": "not-an-email",
        "expectedRevenue": "bad-number"
    }
}

### --------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Get All Leads
### --------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/leads
